Roseroad070193gbhg3flcg8255j05gf6f2r2xrejgt81806272015-04-03T05:08:46ZThe Dragon Demands5014364/* References */[[Image:Roseroad.png|thumb|right|200px|A map showing the Roseroad on the continent of Westeros.]]
The '''Roseroad''' is a major highway in the [[Seven Kingdoms]], second in size only to the [[Kingsroad]]. It connects the two largest cities in the realm, [[King's Landing]] and [[Oldtown]], via [[Highgarden]], the seat of [[House Tyrell]]. The Roseroad meets the [[Searoad]] at Highgarden, which travelers coming up from the south would take if they wanted to head north along the coast to [[Casterly Rock]] and [[Lannisport]] (those directly traveling from King's Landing to Lannisport would take the [[Goldroad]] to the north).

The road does not directly begin at King's Landing, instead splitting off from the Kingsroad just south of the mouth of the [[Blackwater Rush|Blackwater]] River, under the eves of the [[Kingswood]] (King's Landing itself is on the north side of the river's mouth). From there it runs southwest across much of [[the Reach]] until it arrives at Highgarden.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season1/#!/locations/kings-landing/ HBO viewers guide, season 1 map, King's Landing entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

The road crosses the great [[Mander]] River twice on the way from King's Landing to Highgarden: it crosses from the southern to northern bank of the upper Mander just west of [[Bitterbridge]] in the central Reach, then later on it crosses back across the Mander again from the northern bank to the southern bank just before it comes to Highgarden.

The Roseroad runs almost east-to-west between King's Landing and Bitterbridge, though always in a generally southwestern direction. However, after Bitterbridge the road angles much more sharply in a southwestern direction as it continues through Highgarden and on to Oldtown further to the southwest. As Oldtown is located on the west bank of the [[Honeywine]] River, the Roseroad also has to cross that river just before it reaches the city.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season1/#!/locations/highgarden/ HBO viewers guide, season 1 map, Highgarden entry]&lt;/ref&gt;
